grades.title: RELY 5922R 10000 Black
grades.summary: Density 959 kg/m3, MFR(5 kg) 0.2 g/10 min
grades.description:
SABIC® Vestolen A RELY 5922R 10000 is a grade which has a high density and a bimodal distribution of the molecular mass. 
Due to its resistance against slow crack growth (SCG) the material SABIC® Vestolen A RELY 5922R 10000 is considered as PE100-RC and may be used for no dig applications. 
Moreover it may be used for the production of thick walled (large diameter and low SDR) pipes for infrastructure and industrial application due to its low sagging characteristics and it shows favorable processing behavior. 
This material meets (inter)national standards for use in gas, drinking water and waste water piping.MRS class ISO 12162 MPa = 10.0 (PE 100). 

This product is not intended for and must not be used in any pharmaceutical/medical applications.

grades.title: RELY 5944HT 10000 Black
grades.summary: Density 959 kg/m3, MFR(5 kg) 0.2 g/10 min
grades.description:
SABIC® Vestolen A RELY 5944HT 10000 is a grade which has a high density and a bimodal distribution of the molecular mass.
Due to its heat ageing stability SABIC® Vestolen A RELY 5944HT 10000 is typically used for industrial pipes and other applications where increased thermal load can be expected, such as high voltage cable ducts.
Because of its resistance against slow crack growth (SCG) the material SABIC® Vestolen A RELY 5944HT 10000 is considered as PE100-RC and may be used for no dig applications.
The material shows favorable processing behavior and due to its low sagging characteristics it is typically used for the production of thick walled (large diameter and low SDR) pipes.
MRS class ISO 12162 MPa = 10.0 (PE 100). 

This product is not intended for and must not be used in any pharmaceutical/medical applications.
